    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Subject: Update on Your Application for [Position]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the [Position] role at [Company Name]. We appreciate the effort you put into preparing for our final round of interviews.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we regret to inform you that we will not be moving forward with your application at this time. While your skills and experience are impressive, we have decided to pursue other candidates whose skills and background are a better fit for the specific needs of our team.\n\nWe wanted to provide you with some feedback on your coding test, as we believe it is an area where you can continue to grow. The areas that stood out to us were [provide specific feedback on coding test, e.g., \"your approach to problem-solving\" or \"your ability to optimize code\"]. We encourage you to continue honing these skills and exploring new technologies.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in [Company Name] and wish you the best of luck in your job search. We will keep your resume on file and consider you for future opportunities that may be a better fit for your skills and experience.\n\nThank you again for your time and consideration.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\nHR Manager",
